The paper proposes a convolutional neural network architecture for breast cancer classification using both 2D and 3D mammograms. This involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) for classification. The use of multiple imaging modalities also suggests the involvement of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Finally, the use of deep learning (cs.DL) is also likely given the use of convolutional neural networks.
